  · FebtSrruarpShoefnsorufeetSdyl fS21  ·
At the same time, with the meeting of Rafael Grosi, the director of the International Atomic Energy Agency, Ali Akbar Salehi, the head of the Iranian Atomic Energy Organization, a number of protesters gathered outside the Atomic Energy Organization
Mr. Grosi who arrived in Tehran yesterday is meeting with Iranian officials today and is supposed to meet with Mohammad Javad Zarif, the Minister of Foreign Affairs.
In an interview with the scholar, Mr. Zarif spoke about the possibility of negotiating with the United States and at the same time emphasized that this negotiation will not include a change in the nuclear agreement.
Iran's deadline to the United States to cancel sanctions is over today and as officials in Tehran announced, Iran will stop the Alhaghi protocol and inspection of the Atomic Energy Agency's investigators from nuclear centers from March
Rafael Grossi went to Iran to negotiate this issue.
At the same time today, protesters who call themselves ′′ student mobilization groups." outside the Atomic Energy Organization building are chanting ′′ spy investigators should be fired."
Protesters are worried about possible agreement between the government and the International Atomic Energy Agency to continue supervision.
Today, a number of parliament members, whose number has been declared more than 220 people, said in a statement that the government does not have the right to withdraw the enforcement of the law to abolish sanctions.
